This is the 'datatools' package README file
 
1 - Description:

  This package provides some tool classes for data analysis
  and a powerful I/O system based on the Boost serialization library.

    
  SVN repository:

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/trunk

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-1.0
    
   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-2.0
    
   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-2.1

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/datatools/tags/datatools-2.2
        

  This package depends on the 'boost' C++ library through 
  the 'boost_help' package available at:

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/boost_help/


  WARNING:

  For versions 2.0 and 2.1, 'datatools' depends also on the 'pba_help' package
  available at:

   * https://nemo.lpc-caen.in2p3.fr/svn/pba_help/

  For version 2.1, 'datatools' depends on the 'pba_help' package
  but this dependency can be skipped on demand at configuration stage.

  Version 2.2 is recommended (mandatory!) and does not depend anymore 
  on 'pba_help'.
  
  Version 1.0, 2.0 and 2.1 are now obsolete.

2 - Documentation:

  Nothing for now but sample programs are stored in the 'programs'
  directory.
 
3 - Quick start:

  Please install the 'boost_help' package first.

  Configure:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure [OPTION]

    With 'Portable Binary Archive' support (this is the default):

	shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure --with-eos-pba

    Without 'Portable Binary Archive' support:

	shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure --without-eos-pba

    Without 'Boost Python wrapper module' support,
    (we have problems with 64 bits machine at CC):

	shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool configure --without-python


  Build shared library:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool build


  Build production executable programs:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool build bin


  Build sample executable programs:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool build bin_test


  Installation:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool install


  Setup script:

    shell> source datatools.(c)sh


  Run sample program (the correct binary path depends on your system):

    shell> ./Linux-i686-gcc4.2.4/bin/test_tree_dump 


  Uninstall:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool uninstall


  Clean built stuff:

    shell> ./pkgtools.d/pkgtool clean

   
